# Privacy policy sync

When changing how DuskRoute handles user or visitor data, update the privacy policy in the **same change**.

Source of truth: `web/app/privacy/page.tsx` (served at `/privacy`).

## When this applies

Update the privacy page if you change any of:

- Authentication, sessions, cookies, or browser storage (`localStorage` / `sessionStorage`)
- Analytics, Amplitude, Sentry, or other telemetry
- Geolocation / “near me” location handling
- Favorites, user-generated deals, image uploads, or deal reports
- Email sending (verification or otherwise)
- Third-party processors (Google OAuth/Maps, Resend, Cloudflare R2, OpenRouter, hosting, etc.)
- Account deletion, export, retention, or consent UX

## How to update

- Keep the policy **factual** and aligned with shipped behavior (including stating that there is no in-product account deletion if that remains true).
- Bump the **Last updated** date when material sections change.
- Do not invent legal claims the product does not implement.
